ZEN-16125 - Tuning. Ensure minTimeBetweenX is under a second

* Ensure minTimeBetweenBroadcast and minTimeBetweenNotification is under a second
* Only consider the past 60 seconds of client ID when counting unique clients (was 600 seconds)
* Bump highCollisionMark from 200k to 2million
* Bump lowCollisionMark from 180k to 1million

ZEN-16125 - Set default minTimeBetweenBroadcast and minTimeBetweenNotification from 50ms to 500ms.

ZEN-16125 - perClientMaxBacklogSize defaults to dynamic thresholding

* perClientMaxBacklogSize, if unset (or zero or negative), will use a dynamic threshold, based on the number of unique recent clients.
* Expose the client count as a metric.
* The dynamic thresholding may be tweaked via perClientMaxPercentOfFairBacklogSize if desired.
* The minTimeBetweenNotification (per-client back-off notices) may be set separately from minTimeBetweenBroadcast now.
* Add prefix to web socket client IDs.
Add collision counters

ZEN-16125 - Count received and rejected; Improve collision notices.

* Send CLIENT_COLLISION messages to websocket client while waiting on backlog.
* Add metric counter for received (not necessarily accepted) metrics.
* Add metric counter for rejected (received but not accepted) metrics.
* Log rejected metrics.
* Give each websocket connection its own clientId.
* For POSTs use X-Forwarded-For, X-ZAuth-Token, or else REMOTE_ADDR as clientId.
* Bump default minTimeBetweenBroadcast from 500 down to 50 ms.
* Add some error handling.

ZEN-16091 - Log and drop unformattable metrics

Implement tcp pushback.

ZEN-16125 - Backoff improvements.

* Backoff for *COLLISION and DROPPED messages.
* One backoff counter per connection.
* Add MaxBackoffDelay config option.
* Bump default BackoffWindow from 30 to 60 seconds.
* Bump default MaxBackoffSteps from 8 to 1200.
